#week-title("Four", "Inner Fermentation & Integration")

=== Core Teaching

The final week of this month focuses on the inner dimension of putrefaction. The
practitioner who does not perform their own personal fermentation will bring
clinging impurities into the laboratory.

"Inner fermentation" is the state of being between two states — no longer the old,
not yet the new. It is an uncomfortable but necessary phase of the Great Work.

=== Topics This Week

- The psychology of the Raven's Head
- Preparing the "Inner Matrice" for the Albedo
- Integration of laboratory and inner work

#inner-work[
  *The Inner Matrice*

  What in your inner life is currently in fermentation — neither one thing nor
  another, seemingly broken down, not yet reconstituted?

  Journal on the experience of being in a putrefactive stage. If you do not
  recognize one now, reflect on a past experience of it. How did it end? What
  "seed" was released from that period of decay?
]

